---
title: Herbed Pork with Ratatouille, Butter Beans and Garlic Pan Sauce
description: Chef Andre’s moreish Mediterranean-style ratatouille is the perfect accompaniment for tonight’s garlicky pork steaks. According to Andre, the traditional way to make ratatouille is to cook the different vegetables separately, before combining and cooking them slowly together until they attain a smooth, creamy consistency. This also helps the veg keep their own individual flavour. Fresh, simple and quick to make, this is a great quick-fix summer recipe.
